..urges FG to declare emergency on roads  The Senior Staff Association of Nigerian Universities has urged the Federal Government to release the balance of N30 billion earned allowances in the interest of industrial harmony. The union made the call in a communique yesterday by its National President Samson Ugwoke and Public Relations Officer Abdussobur Salaam at the end of its 37th National Executive Council meeting at Adekunle Ajasin University, Akungba Akoko, Ondo State. It also demanded that the audit reports of all disbursements of earned allowances be made public to guide government in subsequent disbursements. In its resolution on earned allowances, the union recalled that the Joint Action Committee of NASU and SSANU had embarked on a five-day warning strike between19th and 23rd of August, 2019 to demand the payment of N30 billion being part payment of arrears of earned allowances owed members of NASU and SSANU. The SSANU, however, reiterated its support for the enrolment of members in the Integrated Payroll and Personnel Information System. The union decried the deplorable state of Nigerian roads, asking the Federal Government to declare a state of emergency on roads.  SSANU, NASU threaten ‘mother of all strikes’, demands N30bn earned allowance NASU demands fairness in earned allowances disbursement SSANU, NASU protest at UI, demand N30bn allowance Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.